\begin{parts}
\item Anil changes \$830 into euros when the exchange rate is $1 \text{ euro} = \$1.16$ .
He spends 500 euros.
He then changes the remaining money back into dollars at the same exchange rate.

Work out how much, in dollars, Anil receives.

\AnswerLine[\$][]
\Marks{3}

\item In 2021, Anil earns \$37\,000.

\begin{subparts}
\item He spends \$12\,400 on bills in 2021.

Calculate the percentage of his earnings he spends on bills.

\AnswerLine[][\%]
\Marks{2}

\item His earnings of \$37\,000 increase by 3.2\% in 2022.

Calculate his earnings in 2022.

\AnswerLine[\$][]
\Marks{2}
\end{subparts}

\item Anil invests \$3500 in an account that pays a rate of 2.4\% per year compound interest.

\begin{subparts}
\item Calculate the total interest earned at the end of 5 years.

\AnswerLine[\$][]
\Marks{3}

\item Find the number of complete years before Anil has at least \$5000 in this account.

\AnswerLine[][years]
\Marks{3}
\end{subparts}

