\begin{parts}
\item 
\begin{InsertScreenShot}
    \relincludegraphics{Figures/Q05-a.png}
\end{InsertScreenShot}
A cone has base diameter 8 cm and perpendicular height 15 cm.

\begin{subparts}
\item Calculate the volume of the cone.
[The volume, $V$, of a cone with radius $r$ and height $h$ is $V = \frac{1}{3}\pi r^2 h$.]

\AnswerLine[][cm$^3$]
\Marks{2}

\item A label completely covers the curved surface area of the cone.

Calculate the area of the label as a percentage of the total surface area of the cone.
[The curved surface area, $A$, of a cone with radius $r$ and slant height $l$ is $A = \pi rl$.]

\AnswerLine[][\%]
\Marks{5}
\end{subparts}

\item 
\begin{InsertScreenShot}
    \relincludegraphics{Figures/Q05-b.png}
\end{InsertScreenShot}
An empty cylindrical container has radius 0.45 m.
300 litres of water is poured into the container at a rate of 375 ml per second.

\begin{subparts}
\item Find the time taken, in minutes and seconds, for all the water to be poured into the container.

\AnswerLine[][min \hspace{2cm} \dots\dots s]
\Marks{3}

\item Calculate the height of the water in the container.

\AnswerLine[][m]
\Marks{3}
\end{subparts}

\end{parts}

